    - rid: 1523350325141963752
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Hello, i've heard that someone from your village has problem to solve.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 1523350325141963753
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: 'Welcome to my inn, traveler. I see that good Viridan helped you to
          come to our town. Yes, you are right, there is old barbarian who need help.
          He lives in old brown house, to the north from inn. '
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 1523350325141963754
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Great, i will visit him.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 1523350325141963755
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Do you need something more?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 1523350325141963756
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Were there any rumors going around?
    - rid: 1523350325141963757
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: I want something to eat.
    - rid: 1523350325141963758
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: See you.
    - rid: 1523350325141963759
      type: {class: RandomItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Flow, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data: 
    - rid: 1523350325141963760
      type: {class: RandomItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Flow, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data: 
    - rid: 1523350325141963761
      type: {class: RandomItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Flow, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data: 
    - rid: 1523350325141963762
      type: {class: RandomItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Flow, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data: 
    - rid: 1523350325141963763
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: "Someone dug up the Black Knight\u2019s grave in the old cemetery\u2026
          but the coffin was empty."
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 1523350325141963764
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: "Bob, an old miner, swears something\u2019s glowing deep in the abandoned
          mine \u2014 not gold, something brighter. He hasn\u2019t been seen since"
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 1523350325141963765
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: "The wizard across the river is looking for someone to bring him \u2018something
          living\u2026 and cursed.\u2019 Best not to ask why..."
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 1523350325141963766
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: "An innkeeper up north says something scratches at his doors every
          night\u2026 but the rooms are always empty."
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 1523350325141963767
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: We have pumpkins. Would you like to buy some?
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
    - rid: 1523350325141963768
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Yes, please. *10gp*
    - rid: 1523350325141963769
      type: {class: OptionItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: I can't afford it, I'll come back when I get some gold.
    - rid: 1523350325141963770
      type: {class: ConversationItem, ns: EasyTalk.Nodes.Common, asm: games.okitoki.EasyTalk}
      data:
        text: Here you are.
        audioClip: {fileID: 0}
        audioClipFile: 
        audioAssetID: 0
--- !u!114 &7584897069484490361
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e5800231a05eaae43b00503881229245, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  originalLanguage: en
  translationSets:
  - counter: 34
    languageCode: en
    translations:
    - id: 0
      language: en
      text: Jimbo
    - id: 1
      language: en
      text: Hello! I'm looking for new adventures, but your board outside inn is
        empty. Have you heard of any work in the area?
    - id: 2
      language: en
      text: Bartender
    - id: 3
      language: en
      text: Welcome to my inn, traveler. I see that good Viridan helped you to come
        to our town. Unfortunetly, all quests are done. There was another traveler,
        mighty barbarian with great sword any mighty head, who did all of them.
    - id: 4
      language: en
      text: Damn, here we go again... So what, should we go to next town?
    - id: 5
      language: en
      text: Ask him again, maybe we can talk to this barbarian? Maybe he has some
        job to do?
    - id: 6
      language: en
      text: Okay then, say goodbye and let's move on.
    - id: 7
      language: en
      text: Narrator
    - id: 8
      language: en
      text: Are you sure? I think we should go to that barbarian. Maybe we can train
        with him or something? As a patron, you should do everything you can to make
        sure your man trains and gains fame.
    - id: 9
      language: en
      text: You again? We don't need your help. Trust me, I know what I am doing.
    - id: 10
      language: en
      text: Maybe you are right. Hey Jimbo, ask him about this barbarian, where he
        is, what is his name, everything.
    - id: 11
      language: en
      text: Why are we still here?
    - id: 12
      language: en
      text: Hello, i've heard that someone from your village has problem to solve.
    - id: 13
      language: en
      text: 'Welcome to my inn, traveler. I see that good Viridan helped you to come
        to our town. Yes, you are right, there is old barbarian who need help. He
        lives in old brown house, to the north from inn. '
    - id: 14
      language: en
      text: Great, i will visit him.
    - id: 15
      language: en
      text: Do you need something more?
    - id: 16
      language: en
      text: Were there any rumors going around?
    - id: 17
      language: en
      text: I want something to eat.
    - id: 18
      language: en
      text: See you.
    - id: 19
      language: en
      text: "Someone dug up the Black Knight\u2019s grave in the old cemetery\u2026
        but the coffin was empty."
    - id: 20
      language: en
      text: "Bob, an old miner, swears something\u2019s glowing deep in the abandoned
        mine \u2014 not gold, something brighter. He hasn\u2019t been seen since"
    - id: 21
      language: en
      text: "The wizard across the river is looking for someone to bring him \u2018something
        living\u2026 and cursed.\u2019 Best not to ask why..."
    - id: 22
      language: en
      text: "An innkeeper up north says something scratches at his doors every night\u2026
        but the rooms are always empty."
    - id: 23
      language: en
      text: We have potatoes, turnip and corn.
    - id: 24
      language: en
      text: Give me potato.
    - id: 25
      language: en
      text: Turnip sounds good.
    - id: 26
      language: en
      text: I'd like some corn, please.
    - id: 27
      language: en
      text: Give me potato. *2gp*
    - id: 28
      language: en
      text: Turnip sounds good. *3gp*
    - id: 29
      language: en
      text: I'd like some corn, please. *5gp*
    - id: 30
      language: en
      text: I can't afford it, I'll come back when I get some gold.
    - id: 31
      language: en
      text: We have pumpkins. Would you like to buy some?
    - id: 32
      language: en
      text: Yes, please. *10gp*
    - id: 33
      language: en
      text: Here you are.
